PART I — DEFINITIONS

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 1 — Definitions

For the purposes of this Licence Agreement, the following terms shall have the
meanings ascribed to them below:

1.1  "Qantas Virtual" or "QFV" refers to Qantas Virtual Airline, an
     independent virtual airline organisation operating within the VATSIM
     network under the VATPAC region, established in 2025. Qantas Virtual is
     not affiliated with, endorsed by, or connected to Qantas Airways Limited
     or any of its subsidiaries in any way.

1.2  "The Organisation" refers to Qantas Virtual Airline as a whole,
     including its leadership, staff, developers, and authorised members.

1.3  "The Software" refers to the entirety of the Qantas Virtual platform,
     including but not limited to: the public-facing website, the CrewHub
     pilot portal, the ACARS (Aircraft Communications Addressing and Reporting
     System) web and desktop applications, the administration panel, the
     support ticket system, the live flight map, the pilot logbook system,
     the Discord bot, all associated backend systems, Firebase configuration,
     database schemas, data structures, API integrations, and all source code,
     scripts, stylesheets, markup, assets, templates, and configuration files
     contained within this repository or associated repositories.

1.4  "The Repository" refers to the private GitHub repository located at
     github.com/Qantas-Virtual-Airline/Qantas-Virtual and any associated
     repositories, branches, forks, mirrors, or copies thereof, whether
     authorised or unauthorised.

1.5  "Authorised Developer" refers to an individual who has been explicitly
     granted access to this repository by the President or Vice President of
     Qantas Virtual, holds a valid and active role within the Qantas Virtual
     development team, and has acknowledged and agreed to be bound by this
     Licence Agreement and all associated internal policies.

1.6  "Authorised User" refers to any member of the Qantas Virtual organisation
     who has been granted specific, limited access to particular systems or
     features of the Software in accordance with their assigned role within
     the organisation, and who does not hold developer-level access.

1.7  "Intellectual Property" refers to all creative, technical, and
     organisational works produced by or for Qantas Virtual, including but not
     limited to: source code, compiled code, object code, database schemas,
     user interface designs, logos, graphics, written content, documentation,
     internal policies, training materials, configuration files, API keys,
     credentials, data structures, algorithms, workflows, and any other
     original works of authorship fixed in any tangible medium.

1.8  "Derivative Work" refers to any work that is based upon, adapted from,
     inspired by, or incorporates any portion of the Software or its
     Intellectual Property, regardless of the extent of modification or the
     medium in which it is expressed.

1.9  "Commercial Use" refers to any use of the Software or any portion thereof
     for financial gain, monetary compensation, business purposes, or any
     activity intended to generate revenue, whether directly or indirectly.

1.10 "Confidential Information" refers to any non-public information relating
     to the Software, the Organisation, its members, its operations, its
     systems, its credentials, its architecture, its strategies, or any other
     information that is not publicly disclosed by Qantas Virtual through
     official channels.

1.11 "Licence Agreement" or "this Agreement" refers to this entire document,
     including all Parts, Articles, Sections, and Schedules contained herein.

1.12 "Violation" refers to any breach, infringement, or contravention of any
     term, condition, restriction, or prohibition set forth in this Licence
     Agreement.

