PART II — OWNERSHIP AND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 2 — Ownership

2.1  The Software and all associated Intellectual Property are the sole and
     exclusive property of Qantas Virtual Airline. All rights not expressly
     granted in this Agreement are reserved by Qantas Virtual.

2.2  No part of this Agreement shall be construed as transferring, assigning,
     licensing, or otherwise conveying any ownership interest in the Software
     or any Intellectual Property to any individual, entity, or organisation.

2.3  Any contributions made to the Software by Authorised Developers, whether
     in the form of code, design, documentation, or any other form, shall
     immediately and irrevocably become the sole property of Qantas Virtual
     upon submission, and the contributing developer waives all claims to
     ownership, authorship credit beyond internal recognition, or compensation
     in relation to such contributions.

2.4  All rights, title, and interest in and to the Software, including all
     associated Intellectual Property rights, are and shall remain exclusively
     vested in Qantas Virtual Airline.

Article 3 — Copyright

3.1  The Software is protected by copyright law, international treaties, and
     all other applicable intellectual property legislation.

3.2  Copyright © 2026 Qantas Virtual Airline. All Rights Reserved.

3.3  Unauthorised reproduction, distribution, modification, or use of the
     Software or any portion thereof constitutes copyright infringement and
     may result in civil and criminal penalties under applicable law.

3.4  The Qantas Virtual name, logo, branding, and associated marks are the
     proprietary property of Qantas Virtual Airline. Nothing in this Agreement
     grants any right to use the Qantas Virtual name, logo, or branding for
     any purpose without prior written consent from the President of Qantas
     Virtual.

3.5  Note: "Qantas" is a registered trademark of Qantas Airways Limited.
     Qantas Virtual Airline uses the name solely for flight simulation
     purposes in accordance with VATSIM virtual airline policies and does not
     claim any trademark rights in the Qantas name or associated marks.

