PART III — GRANT OF LICENCE AND PERMITTED USE

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 4 — Grant of Licence

4.1  Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, Qantas Virtual
     grants Authorised Developers a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable,
     non-sublicensable, revocable licence to access, view, and modify the
     Software solely for the purpose of contributing to the development and
     maintenance of the Qantas Virtual platform.

4.2  This licence is strictly personal to the Authorised Developer to whom it
     is granted and may not be transferred, assigned, sublicensed, or delegated
     to any other person or entity under any circumstances.

4.3  This licence is conditional upon the Authorised Developer's continued
     compliance with all terms of this Agreement, all internal Qantas Virtual
     policies, and all applicable VATSIM regulations.

4.4  This licence may be revoked at any time, with or without notice, by the
     President or Vice President of Qantas Virtual, at their sole discretion.

Article 5 — Permitted Uses

5.1  Authorised Developers are permitted to:

     (a) Clone the repository to their personal development machine for the
         sole purpose of contributing to the Qantas Virtual platform;

     (b) View, read, and analyse the source code for the purpose of
         understanding system architecture and contributing improvements;

     (c) Modify the source code for the purpose of fixing bugs, implementing
         approved features, and improving the platform, subject to the review
         and approval process defined in the Qantas Virtual development
         guidelines;

     (d) Submit pull requests to the repository in accordance with the
         Qantas Virtual pull request guidelines;

     (e) Run the Software locally on their personal development machine
         solely for testing and development purposes.

5.2  Authorised Users are permitted to:

     (a) Access and use the Software through its intended interfaces (website,
         CrewHub portal, ACARS system) in accordance with their assigned role;

     (b) Use the Software for its intended purpose of participating in virtual
         airline activities within the Qantas Virtual organisation.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PART IV — RESTRICTIONS AND PROHIBITIONS

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 6 — Absolute Prohibitions

The following actions are strictly and absolutely prohibited without exception.
No implied permission, assumed consent, or claimed justification shall
constitute an authorisation for any of the following:

6.1  COPYING AND REPRODUCTION
     You must not copy, reproduce, duplicate, replicate, or otherwise create
     copies of the Software or any portion thereof, in whole or in part, in
     any form or medium, whether digital, printed, or otherwise, except as
     expressly permitted under Article 5 of this Agreement.

6.2  DISTRIBUTION
     You must not distribute, publish, transmit, broadcast, disseminate,
     share, upload, or otherwise make available the Software or any portion
     thereof to any person, entity, or system that has not been explicitly
     authorised by the President or Vice President of Qantas Virtual.

6.3  PUBLIC DISCLOSURE
     You must not publish, post, share, or disclose any portion of the
     Software, its source code, its architecture, its internal logic, its
     credentials, its configuration, or any Confidential Information on any
     public platform, forum, website, social media platform, messaging service,
     or any other medium accessible to persons outside the Qantas Virtual
     development team.

6.4  COMMERCIAL USE
     You must not use the Software or any portion thereof for any Commercial
     Use whatsoever. The Software is developed exclusively for the non-profit
     virtual aviation simulation activities of Qantas Virtual Airline and must
     not be used to generate revenue in any form.

6.5  DERIVATIVE WORKS
     You must not create, develop, distribute, or publish any Derivative Work
     based upon the Software or any portion thereof without the prior written
     consent of the President of Qantas Virtual. This prohibition applies
     regardless of the extent of modification, the purpose of the Derivative
     Work, or the medium in which it is expressed.

6.6  FORKING
     You must not fork this repository or create any unauthorised copy or
     mirror of this repository on GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, or any other
     version control platform or hosting service.

6.7  REVERSE ENGINEERING
     You must not reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or otherwise
     attempt to derive the source code, underlying logic, algorithms, or
     architecture of any compiled or obfuscated portion of the Software.

6.8  CREDENTIAL MISUSE
     You must not extract, share, store insecurely, publish, or misuse any
     API keys, Firebase credentials, authentication tokens, database URLs,
     passwords, or any other credentials or secrets contained within or
     associated with the Software.

6.9  UNAUTHORISED ACCESS
     You must not attempt to access any portion of the Software, its backend
     systems, its database, its admin panel, or any associated systems for
     which you have not been explicitly authorised, regardless of technical
     feasibility.

6.10 CIRCUMVENTION OF ACCESS CONTROLS
     You must not attempt to circumvent, bypass, disable, or otherwise
     subvert any access control, authentication mechanism, authorisation
     check, role restriction, or security measure implemented within the
     Software.

6.11 IMPERSONATION
     You must not use the Software to impersonate any member of Qantas
     Virtual, any VATSIM official, any real-world aviation authority, or
     any other person or organisation.

6.12 MALICIOUS USE
     You must not use the Software or access to the repository to introduce
     malicious code, malware, backdoors, logic bombs, or any other harmful
     software into the platform or its associated systems.

6.13 DATA HARVESTING
     You must not harvest, scrape, extract, or collect any data from the
     Software, its database, or its associated systems for any purpose other
     than that which is expressly required for your authorised development
     activities.

6.14 TRANSFER OF ACCESS
     You must not share, transfer, or provide your repository access,
     credentials, or any authentication tokens to any other person, including
     other members of the Qantas Virtual organisation, without the explicit
     written authorisation of the President or Vice President.

6.15 COMPETING PLATFORMS
     You must not use knowledge of or access to the Software, its
     architecture, its features, or its Confidential Information to develop,
     assist in developing, or contribute to any competing virtual airline
     platform or any platform that replicates or substantially imitates the
     functionality of the Qantas Virtual platform.

6.16 USE AFTER TERMINATION
     You must not access, use, or retain any copy of the Software or any
     Confidential Information after your authorisation has been revoked,
     your membership in the Qantas Virtual organisation has ended, or this
     Agreement has been terminated with respect to you.

Article 7 — No Implied Permissions

7.1  The grant of access to this repository or any system of Qantas Virtual
     does not imply any permission beyond those explicitly stated in Article 5
     of this Agreement.

7.2  Silence on the part of Qantas Virtual with respect to any particular use
     of the Software does not constitute permission for that use.

7.3  Prior practice, custom, or informal agreement shall not be construed as
     creating any permission, right, or entitlement not expressly provided for
     in this Agreement.

7.4  No verbal communication, informal message, or Discord conversation shall
     be construed as amending, superseding, or overriding any provision of
     this Agreement unless it is documented in writing and countersigned by
     the President of Qantas Virtual.

