PART V — CONFIDENTIALITY

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 8 — Confidentiality Obligations

8.1  All Authorised Developers and Authorised Users who have access to any
     Confidential Information of Qantas Virtual are bound by a duty of
     confidentiality, which shall survive the termination of this Agreement
     and the termination of their membership in the Qantas Virtual
     organisation indefinitely.

8.2  Confidential Information must be:

     (a) Kept strictly confidential and not disclosed to any person outside
         the authorised Qantas Virtual development team;

     (b) Used solely for the purpose of fulfilling authorised development
         or operational duties within Qantas Virtual;

     (c) Protected with reasonable security measures to prevent unauthorised
         access or disclosure;

     (d) Promptly reported to the President or Vice President if any
         unauthorised disclosure is discovered or suspected.

8.3  The following categories of information are expressly classified as
     Confidential Information and subject to the strictest protection:

     (a) Firebase API keys, project IDs, database URLs, storage bucket
         identifiers, messaging sender IDs, and application IDs;

     (b) Any authentication credentials, passwords, tokens, or secrets used
         by the Software or its associated systems;

     (c) The internal architecture, data structures, and logic of the
         ACARS system, CrewHub portal, and administration panel;

     (d) Member data, pilot records, flight logs, and any personally
         identifiable information stored within the platform;

     (e) Internal communications, development plans, roadmaps, and
         strategic decisions of the Qantas Virtual leadership team;

     (f) Discord bot tokens, server IDs, and associated configuration;

     (g) Any information relating to security vulnerabilities, known issues,
         or planned security measures within the platform.

8.4  The obligation of confidentiality shall not apply to information that:

     (a) Is or becomes publicly available through no fault of the recipient;

     (b) Was already in the possession of the recipient prior to disclosure
         by Qantas Virtual, as evidenced by written records;

     (c) Is required to be disclosed by applicable law or court order,
         provided that Qantas Virtual is given prompt written notice and
         the opportunity to seek a protective order.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PART VI — DATA PROTECTION AND PRIVACY

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 9 — Member Data Protection

9.1  All member data collected and stored by the Qantas Virtual platform,
     including but not limited to VATSIM CIDs, email addresses, pilot
     callsigns, flight logs, and personal preferences, is the property of
     the respective members and must be handled in accordance with applicable
     data protection legislation and the Qantas Virtual Privacy Policy.

9.2  Authorised Developers who have access to member data through their
     development activities must:

     (a) Access only the minimum amount of member data necessary for their
         authorised development tasks;

     (b) Not retain, copy, or store member data outside of the authorised
         development environment;

     (c) Not use member data for any purpose other than the fulfilment of
         their authorised development duties;

     (d) Immediately report any data breach, suspected breach, or
         unauthorised access to member data to the President of Qantas
         Virtual.

9.3  The Software must be developed and maintained in a manner that respects
     the privacy rights of members and complies with applicable data
     protection legislation, including the General Data Protection Regulation
     (GDPR) where applicable.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PART VII — SECURITY OBLIGATIONS

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 10 — Security Requirements

10.1 All Authorised Developers are required to maintain the security of the
     repository and associated systems and must at all times:

     (a) Use strong, unique passwords for their GitHub account and any other
         accounts used in connection with Qantas Virtual development;

     (b) Enable two-factor authentication on their GitHub account;

     (c) Never commit API keys, credentials, tokens, or secrets to the
         repository in any form, including in comments, commit messages,
         or configuration files;

     (d) Immediately report any suspected security vulnerability, breach,
         or compromise to the President or Vice President of Qantas Virtual;

     (e) Keep their development environment secure and free from malware
         or other threats that could compromise the repository or its
         associated systems;

     (f) Immediately revoke and report any credentials that may have been
         compromised or inadvertently exposed.

10.2 Any Authorised Developer who discovers a security vulnerability in the
     Software must report it exclusively through the designated internal
     security reporting channel and must not disclose it publicly or to
     any person outside the development team until it has been resolved.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PART VIII — VATSIM COMPLIANCE

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 11 — VATSIM Policy Compliance

11.1 The Software must at all times be developed and operated in compliance
     with all applicable VATSIM policies, including but not limited to the
     VATSIM Virtual Airline Administration Policy (VAA Policy v1.5, January
     2026), the VATSIM Virtual Airline Pilot Policy (VAP Policy v1.2, January
     2026), and all other applicable VATSIM regulations and guidelines.

11.2 Authorised Developers must not introduce any feature, functionality, or
     modification to the Software that would cause the Qantas Virtual platform
     to fall out of compliance with VATSIM policies.

11.3 Any proposed feature or change that may affect VATSIM compliance must
     be reviewed and approved by the President or Vice President of Qantas
     Virtual before implementation.

11.4 The Software must not be used in any way that violates the VATSIM Code
     of Conduct or any other applicable VATSIM regulations.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PART IX — ENFORCEMENT AND CONSEQUENCES

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Article 12 — Consequences of Violation

12.1 Any Violation of this Agreement may result in one or more of the
     following consequences, at the sole discretion of the Qantas Virtual
     leadership team:

     (a) Immediate and permanent revocation of all access to the repository
         and all Qantas Virtual systems;

     (b) Immediate and permanent removal from the Qantas Virtual organisation,
         including removal of all roles and privileges;

     (c) Reporting of the Violation to VATSIM, which may result in suspension
         or termination of the violating individual's VATSIM membership;

     (d) Reporting of the Violation to GitHub, which may result in suspension
         or termination of the violating individual's GitHub account;

     (e) Legal action to the fullest extent permitted by applicable law,
         including claims for damages, injunctive relief, and recovery of
         legal costs.

12.2 The consequences listed in Article 12.1 are not mutually exclusive and
     multiple consequences may be applied simultaneously in response to a
     single Violation.

12.3 A Violation need not be intentional to attract consequences. Negligent
     or reckless conduct that results in a Violation shall be treated with
     the same seriousness as an intentional Violation.

12.4 Qantas Virtual reserves the right to investigate any suspected Violation
     and all Authorised Developers and Authorised Users are required to
     cooperate fully with any such investigation.

Article 13 — Reporting Violations

13.1 Any person who becomes aware of a Violation or suspected Violation of
     this Agreement is encouraged to report it to the President or Vice
     President of Qantas Virtual through an official internal communication
     channel.

13.2 Reports made in good faith shall be treated confidentially to the
     greatest extent possible and the reporting individual shall not suffer
     any adverse consequences as a result of making a good faith report.

