     WITH THE INDIVIDUAL USING IT IN THEIR DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITIES.

Article 15 — Limitation of Liability

15.1 TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, QANTAS VIRTUAL SHALL
     NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL,
     OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE USE OF OR
     INABILITY TO USE THE SOFTWARE.

15.2 THIS LIMITATION APPLIES REGARDLESS OF THE LEGAL THEORY UPON WHICH THE
     CLAIM IS BASED, WHETHER IN CONTRACT, TORT, NEGLIGENCE, OR OTHERWISE.

