Article 16 — Term and Termination

16.1 This Agreement is effective from the moment an individual first accesses
     this repository or any associated Qantas Virtual system and shall remain
     in effect until terminated.

16.2 This Agreement may be terminated with respect to an individual by Qantas
     Virtual at any time, with or without cause, by revoking that individual's
     access to the repository and associated systems.

16.3 An individual's obligations under Parts V (Confidentiality), VI (Data
     Protection), and VII (Security) of this Agreement shall survive the
     termination of this Agreement indefinitely.

16.4 Upon termination of this Agreement with respect to an individual, that
     individual must immediately:

     (a) Cease all access to the repository and all Qantas Virtual systems;

     (b) Delete all local copies of the repository and any associated files,
         credentials, or Confidential Information from their devices;

     (c) Return or destroy any Confidential Information in their possession.

Article 17 — Amendments

17.1 Qantas Virtual reserves the right to amend, update, or replace this
     Agreement at any time without prior notice.

17.2 Continued access to the repository or any Qantas Virtual system following
     the publication of an amended Agreement shall constitute acceptance of
     the amended terms.

17.3 The most current version of this Agreement shall always be the version
     contained in the main branch of the repository.

Article 18 — Severability

18.1 If any provision of this Agreement is found to be invalid, illegal, or
     unenforceable under applicable law, that provision shall be deemed
     modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid and enforceable,
     or if it cannot be so modified, it shall be severed from this Agreement.

18.2 The invalidity, illegality, or unenforceability of any provision shall
     not affect the validity or enforceability of the remaining provisions
     of this Agreement.

Article 19 — Entire Agreement

19.1 This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between Qantas Virtual
     and each Authorised Developer or Authorised User with respect to the
     subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior and contemporaneous
     understandings, agreements, representations, and warranties, whether
     written or oral.

19.2 No amendment, modification, or waiver of any provision of this Agreement
     shall be effective unless made in writing and signed by the President of
     Qantas Virtual.

Article 20 — No Waiver

20.1 The failure of Qantas Virtual to enforce any provision of this Agreement
     shall not constitute a waiver of its right to enforce that provision or
     any other provision in the future.

20.2 A waiver of any breach of this Agreement shall not be construed as a
     waiver of any subsequent breach of the same or any other provision.

Article 21 — Third Party Rights

21.1 This Agreement does not confer any rights or remedies upon any third
     party, including but not limited to other virtual airlines, VATSIM
     divisions, or external developers.

Article 22 — Governing Principles

22.1 This Agreement shall be interpreted and applied in a manner consistent
     with the values, mission, and operational requirements of Qantas Virtual
     Airline as a responsible virtual airline organisation operating within
     the VATSIM network.

